 s/2026/05/2026-06.19_Web-Graphic.jpg
UID:RgPCv_z-RLq56GN98AFk0
SUMMARY:Free Watch Party: USA vs Australia
DTSTAMP:20260619T133504Z
DTSTART:20260619T123000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Stars and Stripes are back on the world stage and we are br
	inging the noise! Australia’s Socceroos are no pushover\, but this is our 
	house and our moment. Come out\, get loud\, and let’s cheer the US team to
	 victory together! \nFestival gates open at 12:30 p.m.\, come early to enj
	oy the sounds of DJ Athenz! Kickoff is at 2:00 p.m. Admission is free! \nF
	ood and Beverage Concessions: Enjoy a variety of festival food fare\, beer
	 and wine\, and non-alcoholic beverages from Coca-Cola. Visit Smalls Slide
	rs for burgers\, fries\, and shakes and cool down with Frios Gourmet Pops.
	 Stop by Hearsay’s festival tent for a cold beer or beer bucket or grab a 
	michelada\, wine\, or beer from Gaspacho’s festival tent. Non-alcoholic dr
	inks from Coca-Cola as well as pre-packaged snacks can be purchased at the
	 Community Partner Concessions Booth\, proceeds benefiting Levy Park and t
	he event’s community partners. \nCommunity Partners and Volunteers: Joinin
	g Levy Park is Tiny Steps 2 Health\, a research study hosted by University
	 of Houston Community Health Promotion Lab. \nFace Painting & Henna Art: G
	et into the tournament spirit with face and body art from Butterfly Faces 
	by Shondra Macklin and Henna Station & Glitter Bar \nMerchandise: Event me
	rchandise celebrating Houston\, Levy Park\, and the global soccer tourname
	nt will also be available for purchase. \nArt Installations and Photo Oppo
	rtunities: Commemorate the experience with a photo tour of the park\, incl
	uding life-sized soccer-themed photo backdrops and a tournament bracket. V
	isit our soccer ball music box and turn the crank for festive sounds. \nFe
	stival Guidelines: \nVISITORS MUST COMPLY WITH DIRECTIONS FROM PARK PERSON
	NEL\, OR THEY WILL BE ASKED TO LEAVE THE PARK. PARENTS ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR
	 THEIR CHILDREN’S SAFETY IN THE PARK. \nCHAIRS AND SEATING: No outside fur
	niture. Blankets may be brought into the Festival site for the designated 
	blanket seating area. All other furniture is available on a first-come\, f
	irst-served basis. \nSTROLLERS & WAGONS: Oversized strollers and wagons ma
	y need to be parked in a designated area during the festival. All visitors
	 must comply with park personnel regarding stroller and wagon parking. \nF
	OOD AND BEVERAGES: FOOD AND BEVERAGES: Guests are permitted to enter with 
	one factory-sealed bottle of water. Outside food and drinks are prohibited
	 (exceptions will be made for baby food and necessary medical dietary food
	 items). A variety of food\, non-alcoholic drinks\, beer\, and wine will b
	e available for purchase from Festival concessionaires. \nRE-ENTRY: If you
